<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2960] Spark executables fail to start via symlinks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2960</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current scripts (e.g. pyspark) fail to run when they are executed via symlinks. A common Linux scenario would be to have Spark installed somewhere (e.g. /opt) and have a symlink to it in /usr/bin.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
